The first time I saw you, it wasn’t in the common room. It was in the corridor, on my first day. I didn’t know anyone and you were there, with your friends. You didn’t see me. But I saw you.

You’re all I saw, actually.

I didn’t trusted them and I thought they were going to chicken out and show close to nothing, that Lucas and his Even weren’t going to be as intimate with each other, that their kisses would have no passion.
